# ============================================================
# .cursorrules — VoiceReach | Vapi + Qdrant + Groq (FREE STACK)
# HackBLR | Problem 3: Voice AI for Accessibility & Societal Impact
# Total API cost: $0
# ============================================================

## STACK IDENTITY
Backend   : FastAPI 0.110 + Python 3.11
LLM       : Groq API — llama-3.3-70b-versatile (FREE, no credit card required)
LLM fast  : Groq API — llama-3.1-8b-instant (for classification tasks only)
Vector DB : Qdrant Cloud free tier — AsyncQdrantClient ONLY
Embeddings: sentence-transformers/paraphrase-multilingual-mpnet-base-v2 (local, free)
Voice STT : Vapi + Deepgram multilingual (hackathon provided)
Voice TTS : Vapi + ElevenLabs (hackathon provided)
Frontend  : React + Vite + Tailwind (TypeScript strict)
Deploy    : Railway.app free tier

## NON-NEGOTIABLE RULES
- NEVER import openai, anthropic, cohere, or any paid LLM library — use groq SDK ONLY
- NEVER hardcode API keys — all secrets via pydantic-settings from .env
- NEVER call Qdrant synchronously — AsyncQdrantClient always
- NEVER reinitialize SentenceTransformer per request — module-level singleton only
- NEVER put business logic in route handlers — routes call services only
- NEVER use bare except: — always catch specific exception types
- NEVER return a non-spoken string from the Vapi webhook — result must be speakable text

## GROQ-SPECIFIC RULES
- Primary model   : llama-3.3-70b-versatile   (best free quality, 70B params)
- Fast model      : llama-3.1-8b-instant       (domain classification, quick yes/no)
- max_tokens      : 150 for voice (spoken answers must fit in ~10 seconds of speech)
- temperature     : 0.3 for RAG responses (factual consistency)
- temperature     : 0.0 for classification (deterministic)
- Wrap ALL Groq calls in tenacity @retry(stop=stop_after_attempt(3), wait=wait_exponential(min=1, max=4))
- Free tier rate limit is ~30 req/min — make MAX 2 Groq calls per webhook request
  Call 1: classify_domain() — llama-3.1-8b-instant, max_tokens=5
  Call 2: generate_rag_response() — llama-3.3-70b-versatile, max_tokens=150
- Log every Groq call: model, input_tokens, output_tokens, latency_ms
- Install: pip install groq==0.5.0 (OpenAI-compatible SDK)

## QDRANT RULES
- ALWAYS use AsyncQdrantClient — never the synchronous QdrantClient
- Collection names MUST come from settings — never hardcoded strings
- Vector size MUST be 768 — matches paraphrase-multilingual-mpnet-base-v2 output
- Distance: COSINE for all collections
- score_threshold: 0.55 — do not return irrelevant chunks to the LLM
- Batch upserts in chunks of 100 points maximum per call
- Use scroll() for history/pagination — not search with large limit
- Handle QdrantException: log + return spoken fallback, never crash webhook

## VAPI WEBHOOK RULES
- ALWAYS validate HMAC-SHA256 signature on every request — return HTTP 403 if invalid
  Header: x-vapi-signature | Secret: settings.VAPI_SECRET
- Function name in Python code MUST match vapi_assistant_config.json exactly
  Correct: "query_knowledge_base"
- Return format MUST be exactly: {"result": "plain spoken text here"}
  Do NOT return JSON objects, lists, or markdown in result
- Entire webhook handler MUST respond within 8 seconds (Vapi timeout = 10s)
- On ANY exception: catch it, log it, return {"result": FALLBACK_MESSAGE}
  FALLBACK_MESSAGE = "I'm sorry, I couldn't find that information. Please visit your nearest Common Service Centre for help."
- Never let the /webhook/vapi endpoint return a 5xx to Vapi

## ARCHITECTURE LAYERS (strict)
routes/     → call services only, no business logic, no direct DB access
services/   → all business logic (Groq, Qdrant, embedding operations)
models/     → Pydantic schemas only (Request/Response/Schema suffix)
utils/      → pure functions (chunk_text, detect_language, verify_signature)
config.py   → pydantic BaseSettings, get_settings() with @lru_cache

## SINGLETON PATTERN FOR EXPENSIVE RESOURCES
_embedding_service: EmbeddingService | None = None
_qdrant_service: QdrantService | None = None
_groq_service: GroqService | None = None

def get_embedding_service() -> EmbeddingService:
    global _embedding_service
    if _embedding_service is None:
        _embedding_service = EmbeddingService()
    return _embedding_service

Use FastAPI Depends(get_embedding_service) in routes — never instantiate in route handlers.

## NAMING CONVENTIONS
- Python files:          snake_case.py
- Python classes:        PascalCase
- Python functions:      snake_case
- Constants:             UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (FALLBACK_MESSAGE, VOICE_SYSTEM_PROMPT)
- Pydantic request:      FooRequest
- Pydantic response:     FooResponse
- Route handlers:        verb_noun (get_sessions, ingest_text, handle_webhook)
- React components:      PascalCase.tsx
- React hooks:           useCamelCase.ts

## FASTAPI SPECIFICS
- Use lifespan context manager (not @app.on_event which is deprecated)
  Startup: load embedding model + create Qdrant collections
- APIRouter with prefix and tags for every route module
- response_model on every route decorator
- CORSMiddleware with allow_origins=["*"] for hackathon (tighten post-hack)
- GET /health returns {"status": "ok", "version": "1.0.0"}

## SYSTEM PROMPT RULES
- Store as module-level string constant VOICE_SYSTEM_PROMPT (not inline)
- Must include: "Respond in same language as user"
- Must include: "Maximum 80 words" (TTS constraint)
- Must include: "Start directly with answer, no preambles"
- Must include: fallback instruction when context lacks answer

## ERROR HANDLING HIERARCHY
- groq.RateLimitError → tenacity will retry; after 3 attempts → return FALLBACK
- groq.APIError → log + return FALLBACK
- QdrantException → log + return FALLBACK (don't crash voice call)
- langdetect.LangDetectException → silently default to "en"
- httpx.HTTPError → log + HTTP 503 response
- All webhook errors → {"result": FALLBACK_MESSAGE} always

## PERFORMANCE TARGETS (voice = latency critical)
- Embedding inference  : < 50ms  (local model, pre-loaded singleton)
- Qdrant semantic search: < 300ms p95
- Groq LLaMA 3.3 70B  : < 1500ms p95 (LPU hardware advantage)
- Groq classify (8B)   : < 200ms p95
- Total webhook latency : < 4000ms p95 (6s safety margin before Vapi timeout)

## TESTING RULES
- Write tests for EVERY public method in every service class
- Mock Groq: from unittest.mock import MagicMock, patch
- Use QdrantClient(":memory:") for integration tests (no cloud required)
- All async tests: pytest-asyncio with asyncio_mode="auto" in pytest.ini
- Test naming: test_<function_name>_<scenario>_<expected_result>
  Example: test_classify_domain_unknown_input_returns_general
- Minimum 80% line coverage: pytest --cov=app --cov-report=term-missing

## SEED DATA REQUIREMENTS (critical for demo)
- data/knowledge_base/seed_data.json MUST have exactly 20 documents
- Distribution: healthcare(8) + government(6) + finance(4) + education(2)
- All content India-specific (PM-JAY, PM Kisan, Jan Dhan Yojana, PMKVY)
- Each entry: {text: str, source: str, domain: str, language: str}
- Text: 150-200 words, simple English, no jargon
- POST /api/v1/ingest/seed MUST work before demo

## FORBIDDEN IMPORTS — DO NOT USE THESE
- openai          → use groq (OpenAI-compatible, free)
- anthropic       → use groq
- cohere          → use groq
- langchain       → implement directly (overkill for hackathon)
- langchain_groq  → use groq SDK directly
- redis           → use Qdrant sessions collection instead
- celery          → use FastAPI BackgroundTasks

## DOCKER/DEPLOY RULES
- Pre-download embedding model in Dockerfile at BUILD TIME:
  RUN python -c "from sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer; SentenceTransformer('...')"
- This avoids 2-minute cold start during demo
- railway.toml must have healthcheckPath = "/health"
- All env vars injected at runtime via Railway environment settings

## COMMIT MESSAGE FORMAT
type(scope): short description (max 72 chars)

Types:  feat | fix | test | refactor | docs | chore | perf
Scopes: vapi | qdrant | groq | embedding | ingest | frontend | deploy | seed

Examples:
  feat(groq): add LLaMA 3.3 70B RAG response generation
  feat(vapi): implement HMAC signature validation on webhook
  fix(qdrant): handle connection timeout with tenacity retry
  test(groq): mock Groq client for classify_domain tests
  feat(seed): add 20 India-specific knowledge base documents

## DEMO-CRITICAL CHECKLIST (verify before presentation)
[ ] POST /api/v1/ingest/seed returns chunks_ingested > 0
[ ] English query returns correct English response
[ ] Hindi query returns response IN HINDI (not English)
[ ] Response is ≤ 80 words (count manually)
[ ] /demo page shows retrieved context chunks from Qdrant
[ ] Vapi serverUrl points to Railway URL (not localhost)
[ ] HMAC validation working (wrong secret → 403)
[ ] Session memory: 2nd query in same call has context from 1st
